              "name": "DoNotGrantAllPipelinesAccessToServiceConnections",
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Do not make service connections accessible to all pipelines. If a pipeline with access to the service connection uses a vulnerable component, an attacker may leverage this access to attack other pipelines with access to critical resources. Follow the principle of least privilege by only giving access to pipelines that explicitly need it.\r\nRecommendation:\r\n1. Navigate to Project --> Project Settings --> Service Connections\r\n2. Select your service connection from the list\r\n3. Click on the three dots and select �Security�\r\n4. Under 'Pipeline Permissions', click 'Restrict Permission' and add only pipelines that need explicit access to the service connection."
